page.title: 01 GENERAL REPORT
page.content: {Marshchapel}is a country village in{ {Lincolnshire.}It has two nearby towns-{Louth }which is ten miles away and {Grimsby }in {South Humberside } which is fourteen miles away.There is a beach and sea,which is about two miles away from the centre of the village.There are three general stores.There is a Post Office,a primary school,a Methodist Chapel,a church(St. Mary) and a petrol filling station.This a mainly agricultural area and there is a lot of farming.The A1031 road runs through the village joining together {Cleethorpes }& { {Mablethorpe }which are two well known seaside resorts.This road is busy during the summer with tourists and caravans.
